      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "Since the transaction being bumped is fully signed, we could actually get the size information from the existing scriptSig and witness. This would allow us to not need `solving_data`. The only caveat is that signatures are not guaranteed to be the same size. One way around that is to figure out how many signatures there are, and replace their sizes with max sized signatures. But that may require changes to the script interpreter to allow such a verifier to figure this out.",
